<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-427-911  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 427 911.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 1 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Newsbytes now daily, also available by fax. (Newsbytes NewsNetwork)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Newsbytes News Service (Information retrieval system)NewsInformation ServicesFacsimileDistribution Management.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEWSBYTES NOW DAILY, ALSO AVAILABLE BY FAX SAN FRANCISCO, CALIFORNIA, U.S.A.,andO;1990 AUG 1 (NB) -- Coinciding with the release of a new, daily edition ofNewsbytes on GEnie, Newsnet, Predicasts (Dialog) and other systems, NewsbytesNews Network, the most widely read news wire on technology and computers, isalso now available on fax.andM;The new distribution method, which coincides with the growth of fax machinesaround the world, is designed to make technology news available automaticallyto office desks, every weekday.andP;  The faxed and daily editions mark Newsbytes'400th issue culminating 7 years of continuous publication.andM;The fax-delivered edition of Newsbytes is an abstract of all reports, the topstories in the fields of computers, telecommunications, technology-relatedlegislation, technological breakthroughs, and the business of technology,prepared each day, and consists of a 2-page fax to customers which arrivesbefore the end of each business day.andM;If a customer needs full text of a story, the Newsbytes office will fax thedesired article to the reader for a small fee.andM;On an average day, at least 30 articles are available on technology subjects.andO;Newsbytes' team of reporters in 11 offices around the world ensure that thestories offered are the most up-to-date available.andM;Newsbytes-by-Fax is available in both the United States and Europe for $995per year.andP;  Each full-text faxed version of an individual story requested by acustomer costs an additional $5.andM;Newsbytes News Network is a news wire devoted to computers and technology.andO;It has won in the &quot;Best Online Publication&quot; category in awards from theComputer Press Association in both 1986 and 1990 and is read by more than 5million people worldwide.andM;For more information or subscriptions, contact Newsbytes News Network, SanFrancisco, Wendy Woods, 415/550-7334 , fax: 415/648-2550 or Peter Vekinis(Europe, Belgium)+ 32-2-736-3690.andM;(Newsbytes/19900801)</TEXT></DOC>